Philip_Marsh
Greater Manchester, UK495 contributions
James Bond & Top Gear Called This Right!!
Feb 2018 ‚Ä¢ Friends
Having read some of the reviews before I visited I was expecting something of a let down with plastic strewn across the bay, thousands of boats all floating together and armies of tourists queuing for caves or to see the floating village. Well as you can see from my rating I found the situation much, much better.

The bay is gorgeous; an emerald green with tall, dramatic islands scattered like sentinels. Yes there are plenty of tourists and boats, yes there is a scattering of plastic waste and yes there are lots of tourists waiting to see the caves but if you approach this attraction properly then you'll really see the beauty and experience one of the natural wonders of the world.
Tips:
1. Length of Stay: Do for for at least 2 days (with one night on a boat). If you go for the day then you'll be forced to join the army pf other short stay tourists in a veritable floatilla of small boats racing around the bay. If you stay overnight you get to spend the night anchored over the far side of the bay, tour the bay away from the main crowds and get chance to absorb the beauty.
2. Choice of Boat: I do believe that in this case you get what you pay for. It's worth the extra cash to relax on your own small balcony on one of the larger, more luxurious boats.
3. Rubbish: Do expect so,me rubbish in the bay. They are trying their best to keep it clean but some plastic does wash up on one of the many islands.
4. Floating Village: This is interesting. You can take the normal row boat or paddle a kayak. For my money take the row boat so that you can look around. Also take some binoculars to observe the locals working and living on the water. It's fascinating.
5. Caves: Don't expect too much (it depends what you've seen before but I suspect that you will have seen better caves at home, wherever your home is). The caves do get crowded, you do have to wait and it's best to visit as early as possible in the morning.
One last thing; beware that they are starting to build an airport on the edge of the bay in order to increase tourist numbers. It's already busy so plan your visit sooner rather than later.
If you are visiting North Vietnam then this is a must. I don't give many 5 star ratings and so I'd be surprised if you didn't really enjoy this marvel of nature.
Written February 27, 2018
Stephanie P
