Very disappointing.
Sep 2017
We were really excited about this part of our journey but we're unfortunately very disappointed. We stayed in Ha Long for 4 nights which was our first mistake.
The area Ha Long:
is not tourist friendly, beautiful or relaxing. There are almost no good restaurants to be found. The locals are not very good at English. The taxis will take you on detours in order to charge more. There are bed bugs and other insects in most low price accommodation. Everything felt like an uphill battle for us in this town.
Seeing Ha Long Bay:
When looking to go on a one day tour of Ha Long Bay the whole market is monopolized by 1 company. It is very expensive for no options. Your only choice is a big group boat where you see some over touristed caves, can pay extra to see some fishing stuff and then back to the harbour. All we wanted to do was to sail around the Beautiful islands but this was not at all a possibility. Apparently the laws and this company make it that way. Maybe with enough money it is possible to pay your way around this but we did not find any other options. The tour was rubbish.
I would suggest people to take a 1 day tour or cruise option from Hanoi. Do not stay in the area.
Written September 1, 2017
