2.0 of 5 bubbles
One Day Trip - Not Worth It
Sep 2016 ‚Ä¢ Solo
I took a one day trip to Halong Bay (do shop around the old quarter region for the best pricing).
It took 4 hours for the van to get there. I was unfortunate to have boarded a van that had spoiled aircond, so the 4 hours was hell.
We then boarded the boat at noon. The lunch was decent, but drinks are not included. The boat stopped by a spot for about 20 minutes for canoeing/bamboo boat for an extra cost. It doesn't seem very worth it. Next, the boat stopped by a cave (at least this was included). After the cave, the boat headed back to the terminal.
After a total of 2+ hours on the boat, we are now on a four hour trip back to Hanoi. At least this one has air conditioning.
So for those who are thinking of taking the one day trip, keep in mind that you'll be spending 8 hours traveling, and 2+ hours on the boat. Also, that the trip is really really hot and everyone seems to want to make extra cash out of you.
That said, the rocks are really beautiful. But the boat ride doesn't give you more information about them, only the opportunity to look at them.
Written April 12, 2017
