Don't use Aloha cruises
Feb 2016
Firstly the bus journey was terrifying ! I thought I was actually going to die! The driving was terrible and was overing taking when there was coming traffic!
Healing bay its self was beautiful minus all the tour boats. But we didn't get much chance to see it as on the way back we had to do an inside 'cooking lesson' on how to make spring rolls.
When we arrived we were promised welcome drinks, which we were later billed for. Be aware that the drinks they offer with the meal are not free. Even though they don't make it clear.
The room was the highlight for me was really nice and Cosy.
The 'squid fishing' was just a stick with a line on it with no bait that keep getting dragged under the boat with the current. What a joke.
The tour guy went on to the main land and left us on the boat with no explanation for an hour
The food was terrible! There wasn't enough and half of it was served stone cold!
On the way back on the bus we found smashed eggs in a bag on our seat. When we asked for a bin the driver stopped and the tour guy told us to throw the rubbish out the window!!! No wonder the country is so polluted! To which we refused and they stopped off at a bin 15 minutes later whilst they made us hold on to the eggs!
If it wasn't for the view on the way there and the people I would of had a miserable time. But I could of got that on any boat!
